Desert Island Discs: Tom Daley ya ji kamar ya kasa a batun jima'i
Dan wasan tsalle-tsalle na Olympics Tom Daley ya ce ya girma yana jin cewa ya kasa wasu saboda jima'i - amma hakan ya ba shi kwarin gwiwa don yin nasara.
Wannan saurayin mai shekara 24 ya ce bai gane ba har sai ya shiga makarantar sakandare cewa "ba kowa ba ne kamar ni".
A cikin shirin farko na Radio 4 Desert Island Discs wanda Lauren Laverne ya gabatar, ya ce ya yi magana game da batun 'yancin' yan luwadi don ba wasu 'bege'.
Ya kuma ce zama iyaye ya sa bai da sha'awar lashe gasar Olympics.
Mai gabatar da shirin Kirsty Young, ta yi hutu na watanni da yawa saboda rashin lafiya.
Daley ya bayyana a matsayin wanda ya mutu a cikin wasan kwaikwayo na farko na Laverne, ya bayyana cewa yana jin "ƙananan" fiye da sauran yara yayin da yake girma saboda "ba a yarda da shi ba a cikin al'umma don son yara maza da mata".
Ya ce: "Har yau, wannan rashin da kuma rashin bambancin ne ainihin abin da ya ba ni iko da kuma ƙarfin yin nasara".
Don kada ya yaudari kowa lokacin da suka koyi gaskiya game da jima'i, ya so ya tabbatar da cewa shi wani abu ne, ya ci gaba.
Dan wasan da ya lashe lambar tagulla a gasar Olympics sau biyu, yanzu ya zama sanannen mai gwagwarmayar LGBT, kuma ya yi amfani da damar da ya samu a gasar Commonwealth Games a Australia a wannan shekara don yin kira ga sauran kasashe da su haramta luwadi.
